Ukraine received one billion dollars from Japan and Great Britain .
Publika.az reports that Ukrainian Prime Minister Denis Shmygal said so.
It was noted that these funds will be used to pay for expenses in the social and humanitarian fields.
“Ukraine was allocated 1 billion dollars from Japan and Great Britain. The tranche was purchased with the guarantee of these states under the DPL program of the World Bank ,” – wrote Shmygal on the “Telegram” channel.
